# Automated Investor Advisor

# Background

While we do investments on RH, it’s hard to make technical analysis on all the stocks we monitor. This needs both financial background and consistent time efforts. We hope to use the automated system to provide us with time suggestions when it’s a good opportunity to invest. This also mitigates human affection on market change (e.g. we don’t want to check market when investment goes down)   

# Business Requirements

* Provide technical analysis on stocks behavior. Including use BB belt, average, and monitor the options change (like a certain priced call is placed on certain prices).  
* Provide suggestions on precise prices to buy, price to sell, prices to prevent further loss.  
* Remember the suggestion given, and track the performance.  
* A dashboard to track things.  
* The risk level should be midforce. 

# Design Detail

![][image1]

## Data Model

The DB will contain such information

1. User (user\_id)  
   1. Name, email, phone number  
   2. User prompt (what users wants to invest, option? Long term or daily? etc)  
2. Stock list (user\_id, stock\_id)  
   1. Stock to monitor  
3. Transaction(tran\_id, user\_id, stock\_id)  
   1. Transaction type  
   2. Status (Sold, Active…)  
   3. Amount  
   4. Details (Money)  
4. Suggestion (sg\_id, user\_id, stock\_id)  
   1. Date  
   2. Suggestion  
   3. Signal level (ENUM: Weak, Medium, Strong, Very Strong)

## Notification Flow

Every 2 hours on weekdays, the scheduler system will trigger a call to the data fetcher, data fetcher will fetch the stock monitoring list per user, then query the Alpha vintage API and return the data per stock. Control plane will aggregate the data into the data model per stock, combining the existing transactions on the stock. And feed to Gemini with prompt, prompt should include the ask on every field we need, as well as loss prevention price, Gemini should return a suggestion with Json formatting like:

{  
“Stock”: $Stock  
“Signal Level”: “Very Strong”  
“Suggestion”: “...”  
“Risk Estimation” “...”  
}

We should fetch the suggestions, and return them on the dashboard per stock. If the Signal level is very strong, we send the user a text message.

Data is stored back to DB.

## Analyzing Flow

User is able to view:

* Suggestion per stock  
* Transactions per stock  
* Gain/Loss per stock  
* Request to manually trigger refresh

User is able to input:

* Commit a transaction based on suggestion  
* Create a transaction user made  
* Update a transaction user made  
* Edit stock list

## Sign in Flow

We will use Supabase standard user signup mechanism, we user email to sign in.
